   "source": [
    "1]why are the functions advantages  to have in your programm ?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "fd4c7258-a787-455f-b97b-80df96a6c786",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "--->\n",
    "fucntion reduce the need of for duplicate code. This makes programm shorter, easier to read, and easier to update.\n",
    "The main advanatage of function is code Reusuability"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "726e4436-919c-4648-832d-0900a82b7dfa",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "2]When does the code in a function run: when it's called ? "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "09543f57-76fd-4f0a-83da-1d014030e8f0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "--> \n",
    "The code in function excutes when the function is called,\n",
    "not when the function is specified."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "b0385330-cb0a-4c92-aefa-b80cfe0a1411",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "3]When statment creates a function?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "9dc9f491-6005-4d22-b02d-321e9e32f75a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "--> \n",
    "The def stament defines a function"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "10e5b60d-3078-46b4-9279-8c88069c2d0e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "4] what is the difference between a function and a function call?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "88989600-9ce6-487e-ba62-c9f147f15140",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "-->\n",
    "A function is procedure to acheive a particular result.\n",
    "while function call is using this function to acheive the task.\n",
    "Using a function to do a particular task any point in programm is called as function call."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "55418d20-564d-418d-90c1-bb58280937a6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "5] How many global scopes are there in a python programm? how many local scopes?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "8afeed96-af58-4534-a74a-f633cddebc45",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "-->\n",
    "There is one global scope, and a local scope \n",
    "is created whenever a function is called."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "f366d796-f64a-4b2f-b68d-146affa8154f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "6] What happens to varible in local scope when the function call returns?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "8834fadd-9762-41ac-b5c9-22a78646048f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "-->\n",
    "when a function returns, the local scope is destoryed,\n",
    "and all the variables in it are forgotten."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "dc4910d3-0209-46c9-8152-1687529a84c8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "7] What is the concept of a return value?\n",
    "is it possible to have a return value in an expression?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "4ad5a829-3fa4-44a5-9ca7-d63de11fc9d2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "-->\n",
    "A return value is the value that a function call evaulte to,\n",
    "Like any value, a return value can be used as part of an expression."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "b0b82035-5618-46d2-89f9-74498e8341c5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "8] If a function does not have a return stament , \n",
    "what is the return value in an expression ? "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "7cce9b8b-578c-4f3e-800e-4540089bcdc1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "-->\n",
    "If there is no return stament for a function, its return value is None"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "a60f7111-1d4e-4b3e-b29f-63cb2a39ca4d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "9] How do you make a function variable refer to the global variable?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "2d41d194-ddf6-4c12-b71d-0292300ec5ed",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "-->\n",
    "A global stament will force a variable in a function to refer  to the global variable.\n",
    "if you want to refer to the global variable in a function , you can use the keyword\n",
    "global keyword to declare which varible global."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "3662b46f-e304-4219-b0fe-767098e6263c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "10] What is the data type of None?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "c7e6a2c2-e327-48a0-9722-54e3651400da",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "-->\n",
    "The data type of NOne is None Type"
   ]
  },
  {
